text: overanalyzing everything can kill spontaneity tho
sounds like those psychic defense gigs are real if they're changing costs like it's nothing! reminds me of my mate who's into one too many questionable 'investments', hard to watch sometimes 😅
turning 30's hyped up way too much - just social constructs rearing their head
change isn’t always good tho - some places gotta stay secret like treasure maps otherwise they just become another bland spot on tripadvisor
honestly think it’s kinda selfish keeping cool spots all secret - sharing them online lets others enjoy too, just because something gets known doesn't mean it's ruined!
doubt they're still hidden - probably geo-tagged all over insta now
eh strong disagree mate - we're not just products of our postcodes, right? decisions count too
nah reckon we're not just clay getting shaped by our hometown vibes or city chaos - personal choices play a big part too
nah mate gotta disagree – where you're from sticks harder than superglue sometimes; big city vibe's got nothing on hometown roots
not just wildlife though right? think pieces ending up as microplastics might stick around way longer than those clam zooper memories we treasure
sure nostalgia’s great but sometimes looking back through rose-tinted glasses gets old - memories should evolve just like we do imo
block parties were alright but nothing beat random adventures outside the city limits
